# lexEN License Notice

This repository contains two classes of material with different licensing terms.

## Software

The build, verification, and test software in `src/`, `scripts/`, and `tests/` is licensed under the
Apache License, Version 2.0. See `LICENSE-CODE`.

## Dataset Artifacts

The dataset artifacts are derived from:

* Raganato et al. 2017 English WSD Evaluation Framework.
* Maru et al. 2022 ALL_NEW / ALLamended English Word Sense Disambiguation benchmark.
* Model-panel prediction artifacts used to select suspicious Maru2022 items.
* Glite coarsening resources used for coarse-sense label layers.
* Professional lexicographer review assets collected for the lexEN audit.

The upstream Maru et al. 2022 benchmark is distributed under Creative Commons
Attribution-NonCommercial 4.0 International (CC BY-NC 4.0).

The lexicographer review assets, model-panel prediction artifacts, and Glite coarsening resources
used to build `lexen-v1` are research-only audit and construction evidence. The lexEN dataset
artifacts are released for research use and non-commercial evaluation.

The source manifest in `sources/manifest.json` records the source package, local files, license
label, access status, and SHA-256 hashes for each input package. The release metadata in
`data/lexen-v1/dataset.json` repeats the release-level policy under `license`.

## Add-on coarsening layers (`coarsenings/`)

`coarsenings/` holds optional coarse-sense layers that map onto the frozen `lexen-v1` release
without modifying it (the verified release surface — `data/lexen-v1/` and `sources/manifest.json` —
is unchanged). The **CSI** layer (`coarsenings/csi/`) is derived from the Coarse Sense Inventory of
Lacerra, Bevilacqua, Pasini & Navigli (AAAI 2020), <https://sapienzanlp.github.io/csi/>, which is
licensed **Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike 4.0 International (CC BY-NC-SA 4.0)**.
This derived subset is distributed under the same CC BY-NC-SA 4.0 terms, with attribution to Lacerra
et al. (2020); the only modification is the join to lexEN's referenced sense keys and the reduction
of each synset's multi-domain CSI label set to a single composite class (declared as a change per the
ShareAlike terms). See `coarsenings/csi/details.json`.
